==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*fleuh-, *þleuh-''.  Cognates include Old Frisian [[flia]], Old High German [[fliohan]] (German [[fliehen]]), Old Saxon [[fliohan]] (Dutch [[vlieden]]), Old Norse ''flýja'', Gothic [[𐌸𐌻𐌹𐌿𐌷𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /fle:on/

===Verb===
'''flēon''' (class II strong: '''flīehþ''' ‘he flees’; '''flēah''' ‘he fled’; '''flugon''' ‘they fled’; '''ġeflogen''' past participle)
# to [[flee]]

